---
import type { Ledger, Stats } from '../lib/ledger';
import { int, pct, longDate, shortDate } from '../lib/format';
const { ledger, stats } = Astro.props as { ledger: Ledger; stats: Stats };
const co = stats.co;
const ex = ledger.exclusions;
const m = ledger.ledger_metadata;
const items = [
  ['Forks', ex.forks], ['Mirrors', ex.mirrors], ['Vendored', ex.vendored],
  ['Generated', ex.generated], ['Lockfiles', ex.lockfiles], ['Minified', ex.minified],
  ['Bot commits', ex.bot_commits],
] as const;
const langs = [...ledger.aggregates.languages].sort((a, b) => b.share - a.share);
const primary = langs[0];
const others = langs.slice(1).filter((l) => l.name !== 'Other').map((l) => l.name);
const pending = [
  !ledger.activity.available && 'Activity over time',
  !ledger.agentic_practice.available && 'Agentic efficiency',
  !ledger.retrospective.available && 'Retrospective window',
  !ledger.in_flight.available && 'In-flight signals',
].filter(Boolean) as string[];
---
<div class="note" id="methodology">
  <details class="acc" open>
    <summary>How attribution works</summary>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <p>An evidence ledger, <b>not a productivity score</b>. Every figure is read from <code>build-ledger.json</code> — source-derived, not manually assembled — and each headline equals the sum of its rows.</p>
      <p>Authorship is shown in layers, strongest first. <b>Co-authored-by trailers</b> are the proven floor — explicit, but only present where the tool wrote one, so a repo can be heavily AI-built yet show a low trailer %. <b>Agent sessions</b> from local Claude Code and Codex logs cover that gap (counts and tokens only, never transcript text — AD-9); a repo at 0% trailers with hundreds of sessions was still built with AI. <b>AI-native artefacts</b> are the circumstantial third layer. Line-level attribution is the next phase.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="acc">
    <summary>Commit reconciliation</summary>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <table class="breakdown">
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>AI-co-authored <span class="tag">human commit, AI trailer</span></td><td class="n">{int(co.ai_coauthored_commits)}</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Human, no trailer</td><td class="n">{int(stats.humanNoTrailer)}</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Agent-authored <span class="tag">autonomous</span></td><td class="n">{int(co.agent_authored_commits)}</td></tr>
          {co.excluded_bots.map((b) => (
            <tr><td>{b.author} <span class="tag">bot, excluded</span></td><td class="n">{int(b.commits)}</td></tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
        <tfoot><tr><td>Total</td><td class="n">{int(co.total_commits)}</td></tr></tfoot>
      </table>
      <p>Every commit lands in exactly one bucket; the {pct(co.ai_coauthored_share)} headline is the first row over the total. Bots are counted separately and excluded.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="acc">
    <summary>What private silhouettes hide</summary>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <p>Every private repository renders as a silhouette — shape and signals only, no name, path, branch, commit message, or client name; its id is a one-way hash. A whole-document check runs before publish, and a run that can't pass it does not publish. The allowlist ships empty, so every private repository stays a silhouette.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="acc">
    <summary>What's excluded from counts</summary>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <p>The obvious inflation, subtracted before any figure — itemised with this run's counts.</p>
      <div class="excluded-grid">
        {items.map(([name, n]) => (<span class="x">{name} <b>{int(n as number)}</b></span>))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="acc">
    <summary>Stack signal</summary>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <p>{primary ? <>Primary language <b>{primary.name}</b> ({pct(primary.share)}){others.length ? <>, with {others.join(', ')} support.</> : '.'}</> : 'No language data this run.'}</p>
      <div class="langs">
        {langs.map((l) => (
          <div class="lang">
            <span class="ln">{l.name}</span>
            <span class="lt"><span style={`width:${((l.share / Math.max(0.0001, langs[0].share)) * 100).toFixed(1)}%`}></span></span>
            <span class="lv">{pct(l.share)}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  {pending.length > 0 && (
    <details class="acc">
      <summary>What's not in this cut</summary>
      <div class="acc-body">
        <p>Pending in a full local collector run — shown as pending, never fabricated.</p>
        <div class="pending-grid">
          {pending.map((p) => (<span class="pending-card">{p}<span class="ptag">pending</span></span>))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>
  )}

  <details class="acc">
    <summary>Raw source</summary>
    <div class="acc-body">
      <p>The page renders solely from <a href={m.data_url}>build-ledger.json</a> — schema {m.schema_version}, collector v{m.collector_version}, generated {longDate(m.generated_at)}, history {shortDate(m.date_range.first_commit)} → {shortDate(m.date_range.latest_commit)}. It is served beside the page, so you can diff page against source.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
</div>
